27/08/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The senate on Tuesday (26 August) began discussing draft constitutional amendments endorsed by the chamber of deputies in late June. The proposed adjustments refer to the responsibilities and activities of magistrates, citizens' rights to pensions, private social insurance, unemployment benefits, medical assistance and access to social scholarships. In all, the bill includes over 200 proposed amendments. (Rompres - 26/08/03)
